        <abstract> 
<p>CD finds JT’s discourse "grand and most interesting" [<hi rend="italic">On the scientific use of the imagination</hi> (1870)]. Flattered by what JT says about him.</p> 
            <p>He is "a rash man to say a good word for Pangenesis for it has hardly a friend among naturalists".</p>
            <p>CD is much struck with what JT says about "pondering" and delighted by his "as if" argument.</p>
        </abstract>
